hopobject.body: I stay at home and look after the children acheter viagra en france pas cher Although Wall Street enjoyed his fervour for deregulation, it is now argued that Summers laid the foundation for a series of policy mistakes, including doing away with the 1933 Glass Steagall Act which separated commercial and investment banking. He also strenuously resisted calls for a regulatory crackdown on the derivatives market which could arguably have helped prevent the banking crisis.
